        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 10 at 6:02PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 601 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Canaan, or 16 miles south of Bolivar, moving
southeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chalybeate, Brody, Pocahontas, Collinstown, Biggersville, New Canaan,
Jobes, Hinkle, Hamilton, Middleton, Theo, Van Buren, Corinth,
Tiplersville, Rogers Springs, Saulsbury, Kossuth, Allentown,
Hightown, and Crumtown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
west Tennessee. A Severe Thunderstorm Watch also remains in effect
until 1100 PM CDT for northeastern Mississippi.</instruction>
